vities and organizations to enhance your resume, learn valuable leadership and organizational management skills, make new friends, and enjoy the richer college experience.  You can also get involved with Fraternity & Sorority Life on campus by joining a fraternity or sorority.  There is no limit to what you can do at UIC, and if a student activity or organization you’re interested in doesn’t exist, you can create your own!  Involvement Fairs is a great way to learn about all the different student activities available at UIC and get involved with the groups that interest you. It is held during the beginning of each semester.       It starts here....       May  13  2020        Fire Up with Mora!  Wednesday, 2:00 pm - 3:00 pm          May  16  2020        Fire Up with Mora!  Saturday, 2:00 pm - 3:00 pm          May  20  2020        Fire Up with Mora!  Wednesday, 2:00 pm - 3:00 pm          May  23  2020        Fire Up with Mora!  Saturday, 2:00 pm - 3:00 pm          May  27  2020        Fire Up with Mora!  Wednesday          May  30  2020        Fire Up with Mora!  Saturday                Student Organizations    Back to main content           Find an Organization    Manage my Organization     Officer Transition    Event Planning    Reserving Space    Funding    Marketing    Offices      Registration 2020-2021     Returning Student Organization Registration    New Student Organization Registration    Registration Workshops      Awards & Recognition    Student Organization Events    Advisors                  UIC Logo        Center for Student Involvement         Student Organizations    Find an Organization    Student Organization Events      Programs & Events    Programs & Events    Flames in the City        Footer Menu    UIC Connection    CSI Staff         Contact   340 Student Center East  750 South Halsted St.,  Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: 312-413-5070  studentinvolvement@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    Instagram             UIC.edu link